title: For Sale:  PPS43 with extras
postcontent: For sale is my PPS43. Excelent, near new condition. I've put fewer than 500 rounds through it. I ordered the 9mm version to be a bit more economical with ammo cost. It loved to eat. The original package came with 2-35 round magazines. After much review of every Youtube video avaialble on the PPS43 - and there are many - I discovered that the difficulty in loading a full 35 rounds into the magazine was becasue of the plastic insert used to take up the slack in the original 7.62x25 magazines. So on the recommendation of several users I purchased an additional 3 magazines in the 7.62x25 capacity. They easily take 35 9mm rounds and while they do rattle a bit I have had no feeding problems. So the entire package is the pistol, soft case, shoulder sling, 2 9mm magazines, 3 7.62x25 magazines (NOTE: THIS PPS43 WILL NOT CHAMBER OR SHOOT 7.62x25 AMMO)  BEFORE YOU BUY: The PPS43 is considered both a hand gun and new manufacture so it must ship to an FFL (no C&R) and depending upon your state's regulations you need a permit to purchase a handgun. Additionally, since it is a handgun it will need to ship as such - express overnight - which is not inexpensive. Do your homework on shipping - I am not going to spend time doing quotes to the 4 corners of the country. Locally (Twin Cities) I would be happy to meet you at your FFL for the transfer - your dime. I can ship the case, strap and magazines by themselves which would save some on the overnight costs. Feel free to ask any questions you may have. I have turned my atteniton to milsurp rifles so this one is not getting out.
